    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.02261.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <date when="1891-11-27">11.27&#8212;1891</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>My dear friend Walt Whitman,</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>
                I want, before you go beyond reach of such messages, to send you my love and
                admiration and thanks. I feel that you have interpreted Life for me &#38; have made
                me feel it worth the living. Bless you, dear Walt,&#8212;&#38; I wish 
                that I might bear all your bodily pain
                &#38; weakness upon my own strong young shoulders. I know many who love you as I do.</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Truly yours&#8212;</salute>
                <signed rend="right">Katherine Hardy.</signed>
                <address>
                    <addrLine>Enon Valley,</addrLine>
                    <addrLine>Lawrence Co.,</addrLine>
                    <addrLine>Penn.</addrLine>
                </address>
            </closer>
